DIGEST
SB 507 Original 2026 Regular Session Barthelemy
Present law (R.S. 17:10.1) provides for a school accountability system for public schools and
school systems and requires the State Board of Elementary and Secondary Education
(BESE) to develop and implement a uniform system to measure and report school and school
district performance. Present law provides that public school systems be assigned
performance scores based on multiple indicators, including student achievement, academic
growth, graduation rates, and uses those scores to classify schools with a letter grade. Present
law provides that schools are annually evaluated, and those identified as low-performing are
